src: nɯra ɲɯ-fse tɕe wuma ʑo ɲɯ-ŋgɯ-tɕi
trs: We are very poor like that.' (divination, 14)

src: a-mu cʰo wuma ɲɯ-ŋgɯ-tɕi
trs: My mother and I are very poor.' (divination, 25)

src: ɯ-χti nɯ wuma ʑo tɯrme pe ma
trs: Her husband is a very nice person (very nice as a person).' (14-siblings, 350)

src: tɕe nɯ tɤ́-wɣ-tɕɤt tɕe nɯŋa nɯ kɯ wuma ɲɯ-nɤ-mŋɤm
trs: When one removes (the parasite by squeezing it out), the cow finds it very painful.' (25-zrW, 28)

src: maka tɤɕi qaj nɯra wuma ʑo ndze.
trs: (The dove) eats wheat and barley a lot.' (22-CAGpGa, 30)

src: [si kɤ-pʰaʁ] \textbf{wuma} ʑo cʰa-a
trs: I am very good at felling trees.' (2011-10-qajdo, 3)

src: tɯ-ji ɯ-ŋgɯ zɯ tsʰɤt ɯ-ɣli nɯ cʰɯ́-wɣ-lɤt tɕe, [tɤ-rɤku \textbf{wuma} ʑo tu-sɤpe] cʰa
trs: When one puts goat manure in fields, it can do a lot of good to the crops.' (05-qaZo, 34)

src: nɯ fsapaʁ ra kɯ ndza-nɯ ri, wuma stʰɯci mɤ-rga-nɯ.
trs: The animals eat it, but don't like it so much.' (12-Zmbroko, 100)

src: kʰro ʑo pjɤ-ŋke pjɤ-ra tɕendɤre, pjɤ-nɯʑɯβ.
trs: He had to walk a lot (on that day, was very tired), and fell asleep.' (140430 yufu he tade qizi-zh, 236)

src: kʰro ʑo ɲɤ-ɕar ri mɯ-pjɤ-mto
trs: (The prince) looked for her for a long time, but could not find her.' (140504 huiguniang-zh, 190)

src: ʑɯ\redp{}ʑimkʰɤm ʑo aʁɤndɯndɤt ʑo ɲɤ-nɤtʰɯtʰu
trs: (The bear) asked around (about the rabbit) everywhere for a long time.' (2011-13-qala, 20)

src: aʑo ʑo nɯnɯ ɕ-pjɯ-sat-a ra
trs: I have to kill her myself.' (140504 baixuegongzhu, 117)

src: aʑo kɯnɤ a-xtu ɯ-tɯ-mŋɤm ɲɯ-sɤre ʑo
trs: Me too, my belly hurts a lot.' (literally: `the degree of my hurting is ridiculously high') (qala 2002, 17)

src: kɯki tɯ-ci ki ɯ-tɯ-rnaʁ mɯ́j-rtaʁ
trs: This water is not deep enough.' (2010-03-zh, 4)

src: nɤʑo nɤ-tɯ-xtɕi tɕʰom-o
trs: You are too young.' (150828 huamulan-zh, 28)

src: kɯki maka ɯ-tɯ-ɕqraʁ tɤ-ɣɤ-tɕʰom-a ɯβrɤ-ŋu ɣe?
trs: I hope that I did not cause her to become too intelligent.' (hist160709 riquet6-v2)

src: ʑmbri cʰo ɯ-tɯ-wxti naχtɕɯɣ
trs: It is as big as a willow (its degree of ``bigness" is the same as that of a willow).' (08-qaCti, 3)

src: kɤtsa ni ndʑi-tɯ-ŋgɯ kɤ-ti kɯ pɯ-saχaʁ ʑo
trs: The mother and her child were extremely poor.' (Norbzang 2005, 152)

src: tɤ-ɕpaʁ kɤ-ti kɯ pɯ-saχaʁ-nɯ ʑo pɯ-rɤʑi-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: (The people there) live in extreme thirst.' (divination 2005, 8)

src: nɤ-tɯ-sɤjndɤt nɯ!
trs: You are so cute!' (heard in context)

src: ɯ-tɯ-nɤmbju kɯ [rɟɤlpu kʰɤxtɤndo kɯ-nɯjaŋsa nɯ ɣɯ ɯ-mɲaʁ na-z-nɤmbju ʑo ɲɯ-ŋu].
trs: It was so shiny that it dazzled the eyes of the king, who was staying idle on the side of the roof (of the palace).' (Norbzang 2005, 177)

src: paʁ ra ci nɯ-tɯ-ɤɣɯzrɯɣ, aʑo ci a-tɯ-ɤɣɯzrɯɣ kɯ [ci tu-pe tɕe mɯ́j-cʰa-a]
trs: Pigs have so many lice and I have so many lice that all put together, I can't bear it.' (2005 Kunbzang, 43)

src: ɯ-tɯ-ɲat kɤ-ti kɯ [ɯ-ɕtʂi ra to-ɬoʁ.]
trs: He was so tired that he started sweating (profusely).' (140513 mutong de disheng-zh, 70)

src: ɲɯ-maqʰu ɯ-xɕɤt kɯ, [kɯ-fsoʁ tɤ-rɤŋgat ri kóʁmɯz tu-ɬoʁ ŋu.]
trs: (This star) is so late that it only comes out when the day is about to break.' (29-mWBZi, 41)

src: ɲɯ-xtɕi ɲɯ-tɕʰom
trs: It is too small.' (elicited)

src: [nɯŋa ra nɯ-taʁ tu-dɤn tu-tɕʰom] mɯ́j-pe ma
trs: It is not good when there are too many (ticks) on cows.' (25-xCelwi, 31)

src: nɯ ma aʑo maka, kɤ-nɯ-rga mɯ́j-kʰɯ ʑo ɲɯ-rga-a
trs: I like it extremely (to the extent that it is not possible to like it more than I do).' (140521 huangdi de xinzhuang-zh, 141)

src: nɯ ma kɤ-nɯ-rga mɤ-kɯ-kʰɯ ʑo ɲɯ-rga-a
trs: I like it extremely.' (elicitation based on \ref{ex:nW.ma.mWjkhW.Zo})

src: ɯ-rʑaβ aʑo sɤz wxti
trs: His wife is older than me.' (14-siblings, 200)

src: ɯ-rna nɯ [mbro ɣɯ] sɤz ɲɯ-wxti.
trs: Its ears are bigger than those of the horse.' (20-tArka, 5)

src: tɕeri ɯ-phoŋbu nɯ mbro sɤz koŋla ʑo ɲɯ-wxti.
trs: Its body is bigger than (that of) a horse.' (19-rNamoN, 38)

src: tɯ-ɣli kɯ-dɤn ɯ-stu qandʐe nɯ kɯ ɲɯ-jpum.
trs: The earthworms that are in places where there is a lot of dung (fertilizer) are fatter.' (25-akWzgumba, 128)

src: aʑo kɯ a-laz ɲɯ-sna
trs: I am luckier (than you).' (140515 huli he yelv-zh, 19)

src: tɤru ɯ-tɕɯ nɯ sɤz ɲɯ-tɯ-rʑi!
trs: You are heavier than the prince!' (140506 woju guniang-zh, 134)

src: waŋtɕin sɤznɤ ʁnɯ-pɤrme ma mɤ-xtɕi
trs: He is only two years younger than Dbangcan.' (14-siblings, 242)

src: jɯfɕɯr sɤz jɯsŋi kɯ ɲɯ-mpja
trs: Today is warmer than yesterday.' (elicited)

src: nɯ sɤznɤ [a-pɯ-si] kɯ ɲɯ-mna
trs: It is better that he dies.' (150909 xiaocui-zh, 118)

src: kɯ-mɤku cʰɯ-kɯ-tɯt nɯ ɲɯ-tɕur tsa
trs: The one (apple) that ripens earlier is a bit sourer.' (07-paXCi, 48)

src: ʁmɯrcɯ sɤz ɲɯ-wxti tsa
trs: It is a bit bigger than the Garrulax sp.' (23-qapGAmtWmtW, 13)

src: nɯnɯ kɯ-xtɕɯ\redp{}xtɕi ci tɕe, βʑɯ ndɤre mɤ-ʑɯ. βʑɯ sɤz ndɤre wxti ŋu
trs: (The weasel) is a small (animal), but bigger than a mouse. It is bigger than a mouse.' (27-spjaNkW, 32)

src: ki kɯm ki mɤ-ʑɯ-a
trs: I am bigger than this door.' (elicited)

src: a-tɯ-mbro ki kɯm ki mɤ-ʑɯ.
trs: I am bigger than this door.' (elicited)

src: qamtɕɯr nɯ ɯ-mtɕʰi nɯnɯ βʑɯ sɤznɤ mɤʑɯ ʑo amtɕoʁ
trs: The mouth of the shrew is even more pointy than that of the mouse.' (27-spjaNkW, 204)

imt: bug \textsc{obj}:\textsc{pcp}-say \textsc{indef} exist:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk} \textsc{dem} \textsc{unexp}:\textsc{foc} \textsc{sbj}:\textsc{pcp}-\textsc{emph}\redp{}be.small \textsc{indef} \textsc{emph} be.\textsc{aff}:\textsc{fact} louse also not.exist:\textsc{fact}
src: qajɯβlama kɤ-ti ci tu tɕe, nɯ rca kɯ-xtɕɯ\redp{}xtɕi ci ʑo ɕti. zrɯɣ kɯnɤ me.
trs: There is an (insect) called \forme{qajɯβlama}, it is very small. It is not even as big as a louse.' (28-kWpAz, 149-150)

src: qro nɯnɯ dɯdɯt cʰo ɯ-tɯ-wxti naχtɕɯɣ.
trs: The pigeon is as big as a dove.' (24-qro, 2)

src: tɕe  dɯdɯt cʰo ndʑi-tɯ-wxti naχtɕɯɣ ʑo
trs: It is as big as a dove.' (24-qro, 19)

src: tu-mbro tɕe, tɯrme ɯ-fsu jamar tu-βze cʰa.
trs: When it grows, it can grow about the size of a person.' (12-ndZiNgri, 4)

src: ɯ-tɯ-mbro nɯ tɯ-mtʰɤɣ ɯ-fsu jamar ma tu-mbro mɤ-cʰa
trs: As for its size, it can grow only about as high as a person's waist.' (18-NGolo, 181)

src: kɯmɕku ɯ-jwaʁ stʰɯci mɤ-rɟum
trs: (Its leaves) are not as broad as garlic leaves.' (07-Cku, 91)

src: qajdo ʁnɯz jamar wxti
trs: It is about as big as two crows.' (19-qandZGi, 9)

src: ɯ-mat ɣɯ ɯ-ru nɯ zri tɕe, tɕe tɯ-tɣa jamar, ki jamar tu tɕe
trs: The stalk of its fruit is long, about a handspan long, about this long.' (16-CWrNgo, 224)

src: ɯ-tɯ-mpɕɤr ɣɯ ɯ-fsu jamar ci ɲɯ-kʰe ɕti
trs: S/he$_i$ is stupid to the extent of his/her$_i$ beauty.' (elicited)

src: ɯ-tɯ-mpɕɤr cʰo ɯ-tɯ-kʰe nɯ ɲɯ-ɤfsuja ɕti
trs: His/her beauty and his/her stupidity are equal.' (elicited)

src: tɕʰi jamar kɯ-mpɕɤr nɯ, nɯ jamar ci ɲɯ-kʰe ɕti
trs: A much as s/he is beautiful, s/he is stupid.' (elicited)

src: [kɤ-ɤnɯɣro] kɯ-fse tú-wɣ-ndza ɕti ma
trs: People eat it for fun (as if to play, not as part of a real meal).' (08-rasti, 59)

src: nɤʑo stu ʑo tɯ-mkʰɤz tɕe, tɕe nɤʑo ɕ-tɤ-nɤme
trs: You are the best at it, do it!' (150822 laoye zuoshi zongshi duide-zh, 37)

src: nɯ pɣɤtɕɯ nɯ-ŋgɯz stu xtɕi low.
trs: It is the smallest of all birds.' (24-ZmbrWpGa, 126)

src: kɯɕɯŋgɯ tɕe <aizheng> kɤ-ti pɯ-me tɕe, kɤ-kɯ-nɤndza nɯ stu ʑo kɯ-ŋɤn kɤ-pa pɯ-ŋu.
trs: In former times, nobody talked about cancer, and leprosy was considered to be the most terrible (of all diseases).' (25-khArWm, 35)

src: tɕe tɯ-ci ɯ-rkɯ tu-ɬoʁ tɕe, nɯ stu ɯ-kɤ-nɯ-rga ŋu tɕe
trs: It grows near the water, it is what it likes the most.' (09-mi, 6)

src: [stu ʑo ɯ-kɤ-ndza] nɯnɯ tɯ-ŋga, tɤ-rme kɯ-fse, tɯ-ŋga nɯra ŋu.
trs: What it eats most is clothes, clothes (made of animal fur).' (28-kWpAz, 79)

src: [stu ɯ-sɤ-dɤn] nɯ stɤmku nɯra ŋu-nɯ.
trs: The place where it is most numerous is the grasslands.' (19-qachGa mWntoR, 24-25)

src: tɕe [pɣa tʰamtɕɤt ɣɯ nɯ-kɯ-mpɕɤr] nɯ rmɤβja ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: The peacock is the most beautiful of all birds.' (24-ZmbrWpGa, 84)

src: ama, a-pi kʰu nɯ tɕʰindʐa ku-tɯ-nɤpʰɯphɣo tɕe [nɤʑo kɯ-fse] kɯ-sɤɣ-mu me
trs: Brother tiger, why are you running away like that, you are the most dreadful (animal).' (literally: `There is no one dreadful like you') (2005 khu, 25)

src: aʑo [nɯ kɯ-fse] ʑo maka tu-tso-a me, tu-sɯz-a me
trs: This is what I know best.' (literally: `There is nothing that I understand, that I know like that.' 140519 yeying, 62)

src: aʑo [nɯ kɯ-fse pjɯ-sɯz-a] me
trs: I know of no such thing.' (elicited)

src: aʑo ɕaŋtaʁ kɯ-cʰa kɯ-rkaŋ me
trs: I am the most able one, the most robust one.' (literally: `There is no one that is more robust/able than me') (140425 shizi huli he lu-zh, 28)
